args.prompt:
You are given the ASCII block stored in the variable <query_llm_1/>. Do NOT reveal raw email contents. Parse it. If it begins with "FOUND: NO" output the exact JSON object: {"found": false}. If it begins with "FOUND: YES", parse the actions listed into JSON, where each action is an object with keys: type, title, date, start, end, participants, description, location, email_to, email_subject, email_body, filename, filecontent. participants should be an array of emails or null. Use null for missing fields. Use (missing) in the source is not allowed; use null for missing. Output valid ASCII-only JSON with double quotes and no extra text. Example output:
{"found": true, "actions": [{"type":"create_event","title":"Weekly Sync","date":"2024-05-17","start":"10:00","end":"11:00","participants":["a@x.com","b@y.com"],"description":"Review progress","location":"Zoom","email_to":null,"email_subject":null,"email_body":null,"filename":null,"filecontent":null}]}

Parse participant lists by splitting on commas and trimming spaces. Ensure dates are in YYYY-MM-DD and times in HH:MM when present. If a field is present but empty, use null. Output only the JSON.

